               <head>Revenues and description of Bengal</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh94006886 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4458-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Revenue records, in Persian with raqam annotation, and description of the Province of <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n81059698" type="place">Bengal</name>
                        </p>
                        <p>Comprised of 2 sections: 1) accounts for the khāliṣah sharīfah in jannat al-bilād Bengal 1172 banglah; 2) record of the earmarked accounts of Bengal for the banglah years 1172, 1173, 1174, 1175, 1176, upto 16 Jum. I regnal year 11 (of Emperor Shāh ʿĀlam), equating to 5 Pars [Yīl] </p>
                        <p>Dated oval seals of James Grant at beginning and end: Jams Grānt ṣadr-i sarishtah'dār (sic) va mulāḥiẓ-i kull-i dafātir az ṭaraf-i dīvān-i ṣūbah'jāt-i Bangālah va Bihār va gairah, madār al-mahām sipah sālār-i Angrīz-i Kampanī, sanah 1193 Bangalah </p>
                        <p>Not dated and lacking colophon </p>
                        <p>Additional annotations in Bengali </p>
                        <p>Foliated in Persian by section only; estimated 250 ff. approximately </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ben">Persian &amp; Bengali</textLang>
                  </msItem>
